metadata.name: Morixels Mans #1387
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ‚Äãlayers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: cLAZY MONSTER #13
metadata.description:
This project is Generative Layered PNGs files.

There are 11-Layers mixing together to make many unique 1/1 cLAZY MONSTER.

00-Background - 18 items
01-BackgroundComponent - 14 items
02-Body - 3 items
03-Clothes - 16 items
04-Face_Base - 1 item
05-Face_Level_1 - 20 items
06-Face_Level_2 - 21 items
07-Eyes - 14 items
08-Mouth - 7 items
09-Hands - 10 items
10-Nose - 11 items

So the maximum possibilities to be unique is
18x14x3x16x1x20x21x14x7x10x11 = 54,765,849,600 chances!

Good Luck, cLAZY MONSTER team!

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #192
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.
